      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ULTIMATE ZIPPER (1) drew wide on the back row last start so was far from disgraced when midfield. Had looked good in winning his first two starts at Bunbury and the ace draw gives him the chance to return to that form. PINNY NOIR (6) hasn't been too far away in his last couple of attempts at Gloucester Park including a 5m fourth two back. Has recorded a win and a placing in two tries here so looks well placed. WICKED LOVER (4) hasn't raced since September but should be ready to go on the back of five trials. She was tackling stronger city company last time in but won the only time she raced here so look for a good return. MORE THAN HONOURED (9) is back from a two-month let-up but recorded back-to-back placings in March, one in the city and the other from this barrier at Narrogin.",
